#Meta Arguments



1-----Providers -Finished (Second Project #Alias)

2-----Count - Finished (Identical list of Vms, List of Subnet, List of VPCs)

3-----For_each
     1. for_each maps - Finished(VMs and Subnets with map(object),
      combination of diffrent variable types)
      for_each = var.Vms
      name = each.key

     2. for_each set of strings - Finished(List of VMs, List of buckets, simple way)
     for_each = toset(var.vm_names)
     name=each.key/value(anything will be allowed here)



4-----Depends _On [explicit dependency] -  Finished 

it is to change the order of resource creation(changing the terraform default behaviour)

Please refer to Meta_Arguement-Depends_On folder
un comment the depends_on arguement in VM creation block to fix the issue




5-----Life_Cycle


------------default behaviour------------

Terraform used the selected providers to generate the following execution plan. Resource actions are indicated with the following
symbols:
-/+ destroy and then create replacement 

lifecycle {
    ignore_changes = [ metadata ]
    create_before_destroy = false
  }


------------------changed the behaviour-------------

Terraform used the selected providers to generate the following execution plan. Resource actions are indicated with the following
symbols:
+/- create replacement and then destroy

 lifecycle {
    ignore_changes = [ metadata ]
    create_before_destroy = true
  }






